    "text": "Understanding the genetic and molecular factors regulating carbohydrate metabolism is necessary to improve legume starch content, quality, and quantity. This review assessed the genetic and molecular basis of legume carbohydrate components, focusing on seed starch content. It provided an overview of starch biosynthesis in heterotrophic organs, the chemical composition of major consumable legumes, factors influencing starch digestibility, and advances in genetic, transcriptomic, and metabolomic studies in important legume crops.",
